entries.meaning: (Ireland, Scotland, agriculture, history) A farmer whose lands do not support him adequately.

verbs.description: congest (third-person singular simple present congests, present participle congesting, simple past and past participle congested)

entries.meaning: To hinder or block the passage of something moving, for example a fluid, mixture, traffic, people, etc. (due to an excess of this or due to a partial or complete obstruction), resulting in overfilling or overcrowding.
